When opening the raw of a snippet in Bitbucket, the URL presented will be the following:
{code}
https://bitbucket.org/!api/2.0/snippets/<workspace>/yXqrGr/<hash>/files/<snippetName>
{code}

This feature request is to remove the "!" character and make this URL match the API, at https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/resource/snippets/%7Bworkspace%7D/%7Bencoded_id%7D#get

At the moment it is not possible to use the same "deployment" in different steps.

To make the pipelines more modular I want to split different steps: Like "Asset building", "Copying stuff", "Symlinking stuff", and what else not....

But in every step I need the same deployment variables.
h4. Benefit

You can develop basic definitions and pipelines and adapt/add minor changes only to the desired deployments/servers.
h4. Example

 

