{{    - step: *build}}
{{    - step:}}
{{      <<: *deploy}}
{{      deployment: *Staging-Client*}}
{{    - step:}}
{{      name: Specialties for Client Staging Server}}
{{      deployment: *Staging-Client*}}
{{      script:}}
{{       - doing special stuff on the client server using the Stagin-}}
{{         Client deployment variables}}

Currently, if the user adds a wildcard with additional / it will cause the diff in PR to fail to render. Adding a warning message whenever a user adds additional / in the wildcard would prevent this.

For example:
{code}
/Test/**/
{code}

This will cause the PR diff to fail to render.

However, if removing the / it the PR diff render properly:
{code}
/Pods/**
{code}

The build keeps running if a custom image is used which doesnt have a user set up but using a USER command. There are no error logs present. If the same image is pulled locally, you can get an error as soon as the image is downloaded.

{code}
docker: Error response from daemon: unable to find user dev: no matching entries in passwd file.
{code}

A similar message in the Bitbucket UI would be helpful.

h3. Issue Summary

* When trying to delete a deployment environment variable, the confirmation box is rendered at the top of the screen;
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Using Safari 14.0 or later, go to *Repository settings > Deployments;*
 # Pick/create a variable;
 # Try to delete it using the trash bin icon;

h3. Expected Results

A popup should be rendered on the screen asking if you wish to delete it;
It would be good also to slightly dim the rest of the screen when this popup appears;

h3. Actual Results

The popup gets rendered way back at the top of the screen

h3. Workaround
This issue is not truly preventing the variable deletion, so you can simply:
# Scroll back to the top of the screen;
# Use a different browser to avoid this inconvenience (e.g. Chrome);

h3. Issue Summary

When trying to delete an LFS file from *Repository settings* > *Git LFS*, when clicking on the *(...)* button, the dropdown will render outside of the screen;
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Start tracking files with LFS on your repository;
 # Navigate to *Repository settings* > *Git LFS*;
 # On one of the files, click on the *(...)* button;

h3. Expected Results

The dropdown with the option to delete should be rendered inside the screen;
h3. Actual Results

The dropdown gets rendered outside the screen. Also, when being able to click on the *Delete file* option, the pop-up looks to have its padding off-centered;
h3. Workaround

There are currently two workarounds for this issue:
 # It is possible to zoom in and out of the screen in order to be able to properly view the dropdown;
 # LFS files can be deleted from the Bitbucket REST API
{code:java}
$ curl --user <username>:<password> -X DELETE https://api.bitbucket.org/internal/repositories/<WorkspaceID>/<Repo_name>/lfs/<LFS-oid>{code}
The <LFS-oid> can be fetched from the local repository using this command
{code:java}
$ git lfs ls-files --all --long{code}
